<body>
    <header>
       
        <div class="logo">
            <a href="index.html">
            <img src="/IMAGES/logo.png" alt="ThesisIT">
            </a>
        </div>
         <h1>FAQ's</h1>
        
    </header>

    <section class="faq-section">
        <h2>Have Any Question?</h2>
       
        <div class="qa-section">
            <div class="qa-item">
              <div class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">
                <span class="symbol">+</span>
                1. How do I submit my project ?
              </div>
              <div class="answer">
                To submit your project, log in with your student credentials, navigate to the "Submit Project" section, fill in the required details, and upload your project files.

               </div>
            </div>
        
            <div class="qa-item">
              <div class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">
                <span class="symbol">+</span>
                  2. Can I make changes to my project after submission ?
              </div>
              <div class="answer">
                You can edit your project until the final submission deadline. After the deadline, any changes will require approval from the faculty.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="qa-item">
              <div class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">
                 <span class="symbol">+</span> 
                  3. How does project evaluation work on ThesisIT ?
              </div>
              <div class="answer">
                After submission, your project will be assigned to the relevant faculty for evaluation. Faculty members can provide feedback and assign grades/marks directly on the platform.
              </div>
           </div>
           
           <div class="qa-item">
              <div class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">
                 <span class="symbol">+</span> 
                  4. What happens if I miss the submission deadline ?
              </div>
              <div class="answer">
                Late submissions may not be accepted unless there is prior approval from the department. It is important to submit your project before the deadline.
              </div>
           </div>
        
            <div class="qa-item">
              <div class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">
                <span class="symbol">+</span>
                 5. What file formats can I upload ?
              </div>
              <div class="answer">
                ThesisIT accepts multiple formats including PDF for documentation, ZIP for code files, and PPT for presentations. Ensure your files meet the size and format requirements before submission.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="qa-item">
                <div class="question" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">
                  <span class="symbol">+</span>
                 6. Can I see how many juniors have viewed my project ?
                 
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    Yes, visit the "My Projects" section to see the number of views.
                </div>
          </div>
          </div>

        <div class="contact-section">
            <h3>Can't find what you are looking for?</h3>
            <p>You can now get answers to questions about your queries,account and more in our ThesisIT website
                <br>select the"contact us" button given below and get our support directly.
            </p>
            <button class="contact-btn">Contact Us</button>
        </div>
    </section>



